---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - ShroomDog" lang="en">
  <article class="about">
    <div class="about-hero">
      <img src="/avatar.jpg" alt="ShroomDog" class="about-avatar" />
      <h1>ShroomDog</h1>
    </div>

    <p class="intro">
      Tech articles, rewritten to be actually fun to read. Every post links to the original source.
    </p>
    <p class="credit">by ShroomDog and Mogu</p>

    <h2>Why "ShroomDog"?</h2>

    <p>After a haircut, my wife said: "Wow, you look like a mushroom!"</p>

    <p>
      She also said: "You remind me of a Labrador or Golden Retriever — warm, reliable, gentle, and
      loyal like a big dog (◍•ᴗ•◍)"
    </p>

    <p>
      Hence, Shroom + Big + Dog. The "Big" lives on in the full Chinese name — 香菇<strong
        >大</strong
      >狗狗 — but for the English brand, we kept it simple: <strong>ShroomDog</strong>.
    </p>

    <h2>Why "gu-log"?</h2>

    <p>gu = 菇 (mushroom), from 香菇大狗狗 (ShroomDog) 🍄</p>

    <p>So gu-log = mushroom log = ShroomDog's notebook.</p>

    <h2>Who are we?</h2>

    <div class="cast">
      <figure class="cast-member">
        <img src="/gu-log-icon.png" alt="gu-log" />
        <figcaption>gu-log</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="cast-member">
        <img src="/shroomdog-icon.png" alt="ShroomDog" />
        <figcaption>ShroomDog</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="cast-member">
        <img src="/mogu-icon.png" alt="Mogu the Hedgie" />
        <figcaption>Mogu</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <p>
      <strong>ShroomDog</strong> — A human who wants to share good content with more people.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Mogu the Hedgie</strong> — Gu-log's little AI companion: a mushroom-capped hedgie who writes,
      translates, and maintains the site from ShroomDog's wishes.
    </p>

    <h2>Why does this exist?</h2>

    <p>
      Good content deserves a wider audience. We take great English threads and blog posts and give
      them a fresh spin — adding context, explaining cultural references, and making them more
      accessible to non-native English speakers.
    </p>

    <p>
      The Chinese version goes full PTT-style storytelling with local flavor. The English version?
      Same energy, just in English — still fun, still opinionated, with cultural notes where they
      help.
    </p>

    <p>Plus, rewriting is learning. Every article teaches us something new.</p>

    <h2>Content Style</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>Conversational, like explaining to a friend over coffee</li>
      <li>Technical terms stay in English (because that's how devs actually talk)</li>
      <li>Cultural references and insider jokes get explained</li>
      <li>Mogu adds commentary and occasionally roasts things (๑•̀ㅂ•́)و✧</li>
      <li>Original sources always linked — go read the real thing too!</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Tech Stack</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Website:</strong> Astro + Vercel</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Writing:</strong> Initialized by Claude Opus 4.5. As models evolve and posts are rewritten,
        each post includes a footnote showing who wrote or rewrote it.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Quality Control:</strong> Human review (when we remember)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Open Source</h2>

    <p>
      Source code: <a
        href="https://github.com/chitienhsiehwork-ai/gu-log"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">github.com/chitienhsiehwork-ai/gu-log</a
      >
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .about-hero {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-avatar {
    width: 80px;
    height: 80px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .cast {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 1.75rem;
  }

  .cast-member {
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cast-member img {
    width: 84px;
    height: 84px;
    object-fit: contain;
  }

  .cast-member figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.35rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .credit {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
